to the editor re settling for less by lucian bebchuk op ed dec 27 the settlement with the 10 largest securities firms is as mr bebchuk indicates much ado about very little it will not restore investor confidence for way too long wall street has regarded the small investor as a lamb to be fleeced and skinned i am one of those lambs and it bothers me no end that there are no indictments that the 14 billion penalty does not approximate the gains that were realized by the firms misleading conduct and that the fine can be thought of as just another cost of doing business this whole sorry episode gives securities regulation and capitalism a bad name paul bloustein cincinnati dec 27 2002

